In one month, the number of cases of coronavirus in the region gradually increased.
These cases were largely linked to the Huananan seafood wholesaler market. The market also sold live animals, which led to the theory that the virus came from one of these animals. In other words, it was believed that it had a zoonotic origin. On December 26, a group of patients was observed and treated by Dr. Zhang Jixian, at Hubei Provincial Hospital. The following day, the doctor informed the Wuhan Jianghan Center for Disease Prevention and Control.
On December 30, a group of doctors at Wuhan Central Hospital warned their colleagues about a "SARS-type coronavirus".
Eight of these doctors, including Li Wenliang, were reprimanded by the police for spreading false news. Another doctor, Ai Fen, was reprimanded by his superiors for giving the alarm.
