In the form of claims to cover the extent of the outbreak in Iran, more than ten countries tracked their cases related to Iran on 28 February indicating that the extent of the outbreak could be more serious than the 388 cases reported by the Iranian Government until that date.
The Iranian Parliament was closed with 23 of its 290 members with positive test for the virus on 3 March.
